HEADWORD: Tempered
<hw>Tem"pered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Brought to a proper
temper; <as>as, <ex>tempered</ex> steel</as>; having (such) a temper; --
chiefly used in composition; <as>as, a good-<ex>tempered</ex> or
bad-<ex>tempered</ex> man; a well-<ex>tempered</ex>
sword.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

